<TITLE> Peru will continue to play defensively, says coach </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LIMA, July 14 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Peru coach Julio Cesar Uribe said on Friday that he would continue to place great emphasis on a strong defence. "Peru should start our attacks and counter-attacks on the basis of a solid defence," he told reporters. "That, definitely, is my conclusion after the Copa America." Peru, who traditionally play an attacking game, were knocked out of the tournament last Sunday in a 4-0 defeat by a rampant Argentina, all four goals coming in the second half. Uribe's team opened the tournament strongly, beating Uruguay 3-0. They then lost 2-0 to hosts Venezuela amid a refereeing controversy and struggled to a 2-2 draw with Bolivia. Uribe admitted he had got it wrong in the Bolivia game after making wholesale changes to the team. "I know that in the World Cup qualifiers, I cannot make mistakes and I know that I made a mistake with my intentions in the match against Bolivia, where I wanted to be more aggressive," he sai
